WEBVTT

01:32.080 --> 01:34.970
[How dare you!?]

01:35.009 --> 01:37.960
[Episode 11]

02:00.120 --> 02:01.180
Where's the money?

02:02.790 --> 02:04.510
Where's the money in the treasury?

02:04.510 --> 02:06.770
Where's the money of Great Xia's people?

02:07.690 --> 02:08.490
Your Majesty.

02:09.250 --> 02:11.310
Your Majesty, please let me explain.

02:11.400 --> 02:12.910
This is all problems left by

02:12.910 --> 02:14.840
the previous Minister of Revenue.

02:15.400 --> 02:16.200
Your Majesty.

02:16.710 --> 02:18.240
I have only

02:18.310 --> 02:20.670
just been appointed, Your Majesty!

02:34.120 --> 02:34.920
Your Majesty.

02:35.870 --> 02:37.440
Right General You sent

02:37.680 --> 02:38.400
an urgent report saying...

02:38.400 --> 02:39.200
Speak louder!

02:40.560 --> 02:40.910
Yes!

02:43.590 --> 02:44.120
Right...

02:45.560 --> 02:47.710
Right General You
has sent an urgent report

02:47.710 --> 02:50.240
saying the military rations
have gone moldy!

03:02.150 --> 03:02.490
[Your subject submits the following...]

03:02.830 --> 03:04.000
[State matters rest on rites and war;
yet the frontiers are now in peril.]

03:04.000 --> 03:06.610
[The enemy watches as our troops starve,
their morale and provisions exhausted.]

03:06.610 --> 03:07.610
[I fear a coup if this persists;
my heart burns with restless anxiety.]

03:12.570 --> 03:13.970
They're threatening me.

03:14.980 --> 03:17.310
They say if the rations aren't increased,

03:18.930 --> 03:21.190
they won't be able to defend the borders.

03:22.850 --> 03:25.079
Even my own army dares to threaten me.

03:27.430 --> 03:29.230
The mausoleum needs to be built.

03:30.630 --> 03:33.030
The military rations need to be increased.

03:33.950 --> 03:35.690
But the treasury is empty!

03:36.430 --> 03:37.620
Empty!

03:39.290 --> 03:40.390
Empty, empty...

03:51.620 --> 03:54.350
Tell me, is it time this kingdom
changes its name?

03:55.210 --> 03:56.680
Your Majesty, I deserve to die!

03:56.680 --> 03:57.530
I deserve to die!

03:57.530 --> 03:58.460
I deserve to die!

03:58.710 --> 03:59.310
I deserve—

04:04.070 --> 04:07.600
The problem isn't solved
and you're already thinking of dying?

04:07.630 --> 04:08.560
Then I won't die.

04:08.900 --> 04:09.560
I won't die.

04:09.680 --> 04:10.610
Here's the deal.

04:11.780 --> 04:13.710
If you can replenish the treasury,

04:14.880 --> 04:16.490
I'll leave your body intact.

04:17.079 --> 04:18.510
-If not…
-Your Majesty—

04:18.930 --> 04:20.529
Your entire family

04:21.510 --> 04:23.330
will go join your dear brother.

04:24.000 --> 04:24.470
Well...

04:25.620 --> 04:26.620
No, Your Majesty!

04:28.120 --> 04:29.450
Spare me, Your Majesty!

04:29.730 --> 04:30.530
Your Majesty.

04:30.690 --> 04:31.300
Your Majesty.

04:31.300 --> 04:32.100
Your Majesty.

04:34.070 --> 04:35.070
Your Majesty.

04:40.420 --> 04:41.830
What do I do?

04:43.120 --> 04:45.230
Your Highness, this is a brilliant idea.

04:45.230 --> 04:46.500
To have General You

04:46.680 --> 04:49.390
claim the rations are moldy
at this critical moment.

04:49.390 --> 04:50.810
His Majesty is furious.

04:51.270 --> 04:52.510
Right now, the Ministry of Revenue

04:52.510 --> 04:54.190
is in complete chaos.

04:55.190 --> 04:58.630
Along with the starving people blocking
the imperial carriage this morning,

04:58.630 --> 05:00.360
the Empress Dowager's faction

05:00.410 --> 05:02.320
won't have it easy anymore.

05:04.360 --> 05:07.540
Do you think those starving people
blocking the carriage

05:07.540 --> 05:08.500
was an accident?

05:12.260 --> 05:13.320
It was His Majesty.

05:14.870 --> 05:16.360
His Majesty planned

05:16.480 --> 05:18.560
to make an example
of the Ministry of Revenue.

05:18.560 --> 05:20.960
He previously used
his madness as an excuse

05:21.630 --> 05:24.030
to execute the former Minister of Revenue.

05:24.950 --> 05:28.350
Unfortunately,
it didn't shake the ministry's foundation.

05:29.570 --> 05:31.570
But now the situation is different.

05:33.190 --> 05:34.190
Military matters

05:35.720 --> 05:36.980
and civilian affairs—

05:37.800 --> 05:39.810
they're all concerning
the fate of the kingdom.

05:39.810 --> 05:42.270
The Ministry of Revenue
can't escape responsibility.

05:42.270 --> 05:42.920
Right now they're

05:42.920 --> 05:45.250
also in charge of building the mausoleum.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.680
If they can't fill this financial hole,

05:49.390 --> 05:51.390
it's like digging their own graves.

05:52.000 --> 05:52.560
But His Majesty

05:52.560 --> 05:55.360
chose this exact moment
to strike at the Ministry.

05:58.920 --> 06:00.390
It seems our Emperor

06:01.630 --> 06:02.920
has made this move

06:03.950 --> 06:05.610
with careful consideration.

06:05.950 --> 06:06.830
But it's a pity.

06:08.030 --> 06:09.270
What's a pity?

06:10.070 --> 06:12.980
Just handling this current situation
isn't enough.

06:12.980 --> 06:14.070
More importantly,

06:14.750 --> 06:17.330
once Chen Danian
can't handle the pressure,

06:17.750 --> 06:19.750
the position of Minister of Revenue

06:20.590 --> 06:21.740
will become vacant.

06:22.160 --> 06:23.270
Then people on our side

06:23.270 --> 06:24.860
can fill that vacancy.

06:26.480 --> 06:27.720
Congratulations, Your Highness.

06:27.720 --> 06:30.310
With both wealth and military power,

06:30.540 --> 06:32.940
you won't be held back
by anyone anymore.

06:33.800 --> 06:34.590
But...

06:35.159 --> 06:36.560
if the Empress Dowager

06:36.800 --> 06:38.210
wants to protect the Ministry of Revenue

06:38.210 --> 06:40.920
and is willing to use
the funds for the mausoleum

06:41.000 --> 06:42.430
to supplement the military provisions,

06:42.430 --> 06:43.000
then...

06:44.040 --> 06:45.840
If you were the Empress Dowager,

06:48.240 --> 06:51.190
and this puppet
you've controlled for over a decade

06:52.600 --> 06:54.659
suddenly developed a mind of his own,

06:57.670 --> 06:59.659
would you compromise,

07:01.000 --> 07:02.350
bide your time,

07:03.360 --> 07:04.760
or confront him directly

07:06.600 --> 07:08.480
and refuse to back down?

07:08.830 --> 07:10.270
Please give us your guidance

07:10.270 --> 07:12.330
on what should be done,
Your Majesty.

07:12.680 --> 07:15.000
I truly have no solutions left.

07:15.600 --> 07:17.530
These past few days I've been so worried

07:17.530 --> 07:20.360
that I can't sleep or eat properly.

07:20.830 --> 07:22.000
I fear making a mistake

07:22.000 --> 07:24.600
ruining your important affairs,
Your Majesty.

07:24.600 --> 07:27.670
Lord Chen.

07:28.240 --> 07:29.890
The treasury deficit

07:30.040 --> 07:32.250
is indeed not sustainable.

07:33.159 --> 07:34.620
Those military officials

07:34.870 --> 07:36.570
only know how to fight

07:36.920 --> 07:40.140
and are simple-minded,
only caring about money in hand.

07:41.070 --> 07:42.340
If their provisions

07:42.920 --> 07:44.450
are delayed even slightly,

07:44.950 --> 07:47.280
the military camp will be in chaos.

07:47.430 --> 07:48.510
Exactly!

07:49.950 --> 07:51.480
So our immediate plan

07:52.680 --> 07:54.540
should be to keep them satisfied.

07:57.240 --> 07:58.700
The military provisions—

07:59.570 --> 08:00.860
approve it for them.

08:01.350 --> 08:02.910
Your Majesty is wise!

08:03.600 --> 08:04.400
Your Majesty,

08:04.680 --> 08:05.810
with your approval,

08:05.920 --> 08:08.120
we can finally stabilize the military.

08:09.000 --> 08:09.560
However,

08:12.390 --> 08:13.190
Your Majesty,

08:13.390 --> 08:14.590
as for the mausoleum—

08:14.680 --> 08:16.390
could it be postponed for a while?

08:16.390 --> 08:17.250
-Nonsense!
-I—

08:18.870 --> 08:20.800
We've already agreed to build it,

08:21.510 --> 08:22.630
and now you want to cancel it?

08:22.630 --> 08:23.720
If we go back on our word,

08:23.720 --> 08:25.570
we will become a laughing stock!

08:25.850 --> 08:28.050
How can the royal family be humiliated?

08:28.480 --> 08:30.050
How can I

08:30.680 --> 08:32.080
be humiliated?

08:33.600 --> 08:34.059
Well...

08:34.270 --> 08:34.549
I...

08:35.320 --> 08:36.289
I understand.

08:36.360 --> 08:36.760
But...

08:37.669 --> 08:39.799
But both projects require money,

08:39.940 --> 08:40.960
and I really

08:41.240 --> 08:44.090
can't cook without rice, Empress Dowager.

08:44.360 --> 08:45.550
Lord Chen.

08:46.120 --> 08:48.530
You are the Minister of Revenue,

08:48.730 --> 08:50.910
in charge of the empire's finances.

08:51.670 --> 08:54.280
That's your responsibility.

08:54.630 --> 08:56.590
Use your brain

08:56.630 --> 08:58.430
and find a solution.

08:59.120 --> 09:01.080
Learn from your brother.

09:03.160 --> 09:03.960
Your Majesty!

09:04.100 --> 09:04.770
Your Majesty!

09:04.770 --> 09:05.620
Your Majesty!

09:09.590 --> 09:11.690
What do I do?

09:14.180 --> 09:16.840
I shouldn't have taken over this mess!

09:17.240 --> 09:18.890
There's no profit to be made,

09:19.000 --> 09:20.770
and I even have to use my own money!

09:20.770 --> 09:22.970
I wouldn't mind if I could afford it!

09:23.280 --> 09:26.680
But building a mausoleum
and buying military provisions...

09:26.890 --> 09:28.520
Even if I sold you,

09:28.640 --> 09:30.030
all of you and myself too,

09:30.030 --> 09:30.950
all of us,

09:31.200 --> 09:32.960
a thousand times over,

09:33.480 --> 09:35.210
it still wouldn't be enough!

09:40.130 --> 09:42.140
[Yan millet Promotion]

09:42.170 --> 09:45.760
[People] [Ministry of Revenue]
[Empress Dowager] [Prince Duan]

09:45.780 --> 09:49.230
[Scholars]

09:45.870 --> 09:46.870
Empress Dowager,

09:47.200 --> 09:49.060
is having a hard time thanks to me.

09:49.980 --> 09:51.310
The Minister of Revenue

09:51.910 --> 09:52.840
also broke down.

09:54.100 --> 09:55.430
What about Prince Duan?

09:55.910 --> 09:57.960
I heard that officials were summoned
batch after batch

09:57.960 --> 09:59.750
for a meeting among the elites.

10:01.490 --> 10:02.380
So,

10:03.430 --> 10:04.440
it's almost time.

10:07.790 --> 10:09.360
It's time for Li Yunxi

10:09.920 --> 10:11.680
to help us at the critical time.

10:25.280 --> 10:26.660
Such pitiful crying.

10:27.910 --> 10:28.910
What are you waiting for, Li?

10:28.910 --> 10:30.050
I've prepared the gift box.

10:30.050 --> 10:31.550
Let's go meet the Minister of Revenue now.

10:31.550 --> 10:32.350
Wait a moment.

10:33.870 --> 10:35.120
Is this your idea

10:35.240 --> 10:36.840
of persuading the Minister?

10:37.030 --> 10:37.830
What's wrong?

10:38.030 --> 10:39.200
Using the pretext of offering advice

10:39.200 --> 10:40.800
while actually bribing him?

10:42.340 --> 10:44.200
When it comes
to what His Majesty asks for,

10:44.200 --> 10:45.390
as long as we can accomplish it,

10:45.390 --> 10:46.720
the means don't matter.

10:47.200 --> 10:48.550
If we resort to such tactics,

10:48.550 --> 10:51.800
I'd rather not even propose
the Salt-for-Services Policy.

10:51.800 --> 10:53.150
Have you forgotten, Li,

10:53.200 --> 10:55.250
how we obtained our positions?

10:55.840 --> 10:57.510
The gift box
is just to get our foot in the door.

10:57.510 --> 10:59.200
Do you think His Majesty
would really mind?

10:59.200 --> 11:00.460
A wise ruler and honest ministers

11:00.460 --> 11:01.790
are the blessing of a nation.

11:01.790 --> 11:03.120
If the Emperor doesn't care,

11:03.120 --> 11:04.720
that's his failure as a ruler.

11:04.720 --> 11:06.750
If we don't care either, we're shameless

11:06.750 --> 11:07.650
and unworthy of being officials.

11:07.650 --> 11:09.510
Then how do you plan to present it?

11:09.860 --> 11:11.240
Show your scholarly integrity

11:11.240 --> 11:12.900
and give him a harsh scolding?

11:13.000 --> 11:13.820
That's about right.

11:13.820 --> 11:15.150
In this whole world,

11:15.200 --> 11:16.510
there is no one

11:16.630 --> 11:18.850
more upright and honorable than you.

11:19.000 --> 11:20.060
I'll be the villain

11:20.120 --> 11:21.120
in this scenario.

11:21.210 --> 11:22.540
What do you mean by that?

11:22.720 --> 11:24.960
The implementation
of the Salt-for-Services Policy is urgent.

11:24.960 --> 11:26.670
If you can set aside your reservations,

11:26.670 --> 11:27.750
then come with me.

11:28.030 --> 11:28.690
Otherwise,

11:29.320 --> 11:31.240
don't blame me for taking the credit.

11:31.240 --> 11:32.840
Who cares about damn credit?

11:33.270 --> 11:35.080
If you want me to go with you,
leave the gift box behind.

11:35.080 --> 11:35.440
Fine.

11:35.970 --> 11:36.230
[Salt-for-Services Policy]

11:36.430 --> 11:42.020
[Minister of Revenue's Mansion]

11:36.870 --> 11:38.200
What do you mean "fine"?

11:39.120 --> 11:39.450
What—

11:40.720 --> 11:41.120
Er Lan!

11:42.120 --> 11:43.250
How inappropriate!

11:44.050 --> 11:44.700
Listen.

11:44.830 --> 11:46.630
No one will open the door for you.

11:48.270 --> 11:49.530
The door is not closed.

11:51.120 --> 11:52.350
How inappropriate!

11:53.160 --> 11:54.090
Master! Master!

11:56.040 --> 11:56.510
Master!

11:56.960 --> 11:58.710
Lord Er from the Ministry of Revenue
requests to see you.

11:58.710 --> 11:59.670
I won't see anyone!

11:59.670 --> 12:01.360
I don't want to see anyone right now!

12:01.360 --> 12:03.690
But he says he has a way
to solve Your Lordship's predicament.

12:03.690 --> 12:04.320
Nonsense!

12:04.910 --> 12:06.790
If I, the Minister of Revenue,
cannot solve it—

12:06.790 --> 12:09.080
something even the Empress Dowager
and His Majesty cannot solve—

12:09.080 --> 12:10.440
how can he possibly have a solution?

12:10.440 --> 12:11.300
I won't see him!

12:11.750 --> 12:14.310
But he doesn't seem to be joking.

12:22.390 --> 12:23.990
What did you say his name was?

12:24.750 --> 12:27.150
The court can recruit merchants

12:27.600 --> 12:29.520
to supply military provisions.

12:29.860 --> 12:32.320
The court will pay merchants
not with money

12:32.790 --> 12:34.870
but with
Salt Transportation and Sales Licenses.

12:34.870 --> 12:36.000
With these licenses,

12:36.000 --> 12:37.200
merchants...

12:37.270 --> 12:38.910
Can distribute official salt

12:38.910 --> 12:40.470
and profit from trade.

12:42.480 --> 12:45.000
The world bustles for profit

12:45.390 --> 12:47.360
and the world rushes for gain.

12:47.750 --> 12:49.680
With such solid profit prospects,

12:50.000 --> 12:51.840
they will eagerly participate.

12:52.320 --> 12:53.270
In this way,

12:53.840 --> 12:55.970
the court need not drain the treasury.

12:56.150 --> 12:57.710
Through the merchants,

12:57.820 --> 12:59.600
we can solve the provisions problem.

12:59.600 --> 13:01.000
We can support the armies

13:01.200 --> 13:02.360
and still have resources

13:02.360 --> 13:03.760
to repair the mausoleum.

13:04.720 --> 13:05.520
This is called

13:06.000 --> 13:07.800
the Salt-for-Services Policy.

13:18.120 --> 13:18.920
Your Majesty,

13:19.390 --> 13:21.610
salt reform is of great importance.

13:21.910 --> 13:24.060
One move affects everything.

13:24.390 --> 13:26.870
Salt tax is fundamental to the treasury.

13:27.120 --> 13:29.750
Salt trade involves many factions.

13:29.960 --> 13:33.150
Never before
has there been such a bold measure.

13:33.400 --> 13:35.680
Any misstep could cause chaos.

13:35.900 --> 13:38.550
We must not decide rashly.

13:42.500 --> 13:43.500
My dear minister,

13:44.430 --> 13:45.690
you make a valid point.

13:46.460 --> 13:48.160
The regulations can be gradually refined.

13:48.160 --> 13:50.390
But salt reform will benefit
both the military and agriculture

13:50.390 --> 13:51.750
tremendously!

13:52.270 --> 13:53.840
Once the Salt-for-Services Policy
is implemented,

13:53.840 --> 13:55.120
merchants will have profits,

13:55.120 --> 13:56.680
the Empress Dowager's mausoleum
can be repaired,

13:56.680 --> 13:59.630
the frontline will be
sufficiently supplied with provisions,

13:59.630 --> 14:01.000
and the people's corvée and taxes

14:01.000 --> 14:02.660
will be reduced accordingly.

14:02.750 --> 14:06.410
This is a brilliant plan
that kills multiple birds with one stone.

14:12.120 --> 14:13.320
Your Majesty is wise!

14:14.360 --> 14:16.230
I believe Your Majesty has the discernment

14:16.230 --> 14:17.110
to recognize

14:17.360 --> 14:19.150
the brilliance of this policy!

14:21.200 --> 14:22.360
The Salt-for-what Policy?

14:22.360 --> 14:24.160
The Salt-for-Services Policy.

14:28.670 --> 14:29.390
I...

14:36.480 --> 14:37.140
approve it.

14:38.060 --> 14:39.860
Your Majesty is wise!

14:44.920 --> 14:49.140
[Prince Duan's Mansion]

14:46.390 --> 14:48.190
The Salt-for-Services Policy.

14:48.600 --> 14:50.030
What a brilliant move.

14:50.840 --> 14:51.910
It seems ordinary,

14:53.360 --> 14:54.400
yet it revives

14:54.600 --> 14:57.030
the Ministry of Revenue's
nearly depleted treasury.

14:57.030 --> 14:59.160
It also wins over a group of merchants.

15:00.620 --> 15:03.150
There must be a smart mastermind
behind this—

15:03.190 --> 15:04.320
not to be underestimated.

15:04.320 --> 15:06.510
There must be an advisor

15:07.000 --> 15:08.860
behind that sly fox, Chen Danian.

15:09.550 --> 15:10.750
If we can find out who it is,

15:10.750 --> 15:12.270
we'll have leverage.

15:12.440 --> 15:13.500
In future actions,

15:14.320 --> 15:16.120
we'll have better odds.

15:16.960 --> 15:17.510
How about

15:18.070 --> 15:20.130
I conduct a discreet investigation?

15:20.200 --> 15:20.800
Forget it.

15:22.240 --> 15:25.550
The Ministry of Revenue is still under
the Empress Dowager's control.

15:25.550 --> 15:27.240
We shouldn't alert them.

15:29.200 --> 15:30.090
Actually,

15:30.550 --> 15:33.010
the Ministry of Revenue's
revival this time

15:33.510 --> 15:34.630
will make His Majesty

15:34.630 --> 15:36.420
the biggest loser.

15:36.450 --> 15:38.490
I saw his face in court—

15:39.080 --> 15:40.320
it looked terrible.

15:41.770 --> 15:43.790
The Empress Dowager didn't win either.

15:43.790 --> 15:44.960
These Salt Transportation
and Sales Licenses

15:44.960 --> 15:46.510
generate so much profit every year.

15:46.510 --> 15:48.570
Just handing it all to the merchants,

15:48.640 --> 15:50.750
her heart must be aching.

15:53.510 --> 15:54.550
In that case,

15:55.150 --> 15:57.720
we'll continue to watch them fight.

16:00.480 --> 16:02.360
Your Highness is wise.

16:03.080 --> 16:04.880
The Salt-for-Services Policy.

16:05.840 --> 16:08.110
What a brilliant policy.

16:09.520 --> 16:10.520
Chen Danian,

16:11.080 --> 16:14.190
you've finally got it.

16:15.910 --> 16:17.480
Thank you for your praise,
Your Majesty.

16:17.480 --> 16:19.110
I will work even harder

16:19.270 --> 16:21.070
to live up to your expectations.

16:21.200 --> 16:21.670
CEO Dan!

16:25.480 --> 16:25.870
Look!

16:27.590 --> 16:29.230
[Yan millet: doesn't rot easily,
making it easier to be stored.]

16:27.910 --> 16:28.990
We made it.

16:33.460 --> 16:37.720
[Yan millet: doesn't rot easily,
making it easier to be stored.] [Approved]

16:47.720 --> 16:50.210
We're distributing free Yan millet seeds!

16:50.350 --> 16:51.700
Everyone can come

16:51.870 --> 16:53.270
and get them for free!

16:53.550 --> 16:54.900
The more you plant...

16:54.960 --> 16:55.720
It's free?

16:55.720 --> 16:57.960
The more tax you can offset next year!

16:58.030 --> 17:00.950
We're distributing free Yan millet seeds!

17:11.109 --> 17:11.440
Here.

17:11.750 --> 17:13.680
The Salt-for-Services Policy
went smoothly.

17:13.680 --> 17:15.069
Let's toast to our heroes,

17:15.069 --> 17:15.599
Wang Zhao

17:15.819 --> 17:16.420
and Er Lan.

17:17.430 --> 17:18.490
I don't deserve it.

17:18.829 --> 17:20.730
Li wrote the script.

17:21.400 --> 17:23.160
I just recited it.

17:24.220 --> 17:25.020
That's right.

17:25.069 --> 17:26.829
The Salt-for-Services Policy
was also Li's idea.

17:26.829 --> 17:28.160
I merely carried it out.

17:34.920 --> 17:36.130
This bowl of wine for Lord Li

17:36.130 --> 17:36.640
is on me.

17:39.270 --> 17:39.600
Come.

17:44.660 --> 17:45.660
Please be seated.

17:47.240 --> 17:49.170
With the treasury in such turmoil,

17:49.210 --> 17:50.310
the Ministry of Revenue

17:50.310 --> 17:52.970
has become fish
on His Majesty's cutting board.

17:53.590 --> 17:56.280
How could Prince Duan miss

17:56.460 --> 17:58.920
this chance
to kick them while they're down?

17:59.350 --> 18:00.510
When the Empress Dowager's faction

18:00.510 --> 18:03.510
faces pressure
from both Prince Duan and His Majesty,

18:03.750 --> 18:05.160
then...

18:05.880 --> 18:08.810
Then bringing the Salt-for-Services Policy
to them

18:09.070 --> 18:11.350
will be like a lifeline
to the Ministry of Revenue.

18:11.350 --> 18:13.640
They all think they're acting
on their own initiative.

18:13.640 --> 18:14.900
Who would have thought

18:15.000 --> 18:17.270
that our true purpose
in orchestrating all this

18:17.270 --> 18:18.530
lies inconspicuously

18:19.270 --> 18:20.630
buried in this list?

18:21.830 --> 18:24.480
Once the merchants profit from
the Salt-for-Services Policy,

18:24.480 --> 18:26.130
to save on grain transportation costs,

18:26.130 --> 18:28.990
they'll hire people
to cultivate the borderlands.

18:29.150 --> 18:32.320
The northwestern area near
Yan State has harsh conditions.

18:32.320 --> 18:33.940
Only Yan millet can survive there.

18:33.940 --> 18:36.940
Naturally, it becomes the first choice
for planting.

18:43.000 --> 18:44.000
It's just that...

18:46.110 --> 18:47.420
they don't know yet.

18:48.310 --> 18:49.110
In the future,

18:50.090 --> 18:52.890
Great Xia will rely
on this life-saving Yan millet

18:53.010 --> 18:54.340
to survive the drought.

19:02.320 --> 19:03.850
Why isn't Lord Cen here yet?

19:05.070 --> 19:06.000
I'll go find him.

19:06.960 --> 19:09.110
♪ The joyful drums ♪

19:09.110 --> 19:11.440
♪ Give joyous beats year after year ♪

19:11.800 --> 19:14.070
-♪ Beautiful dance ♪
-Her Highness...

19:14.090 --> 19:17.240
-♪ Brings the lively day ♪
-Is singing about the people's tough life.

19:17.240 --> 19:19.840
Her Highness is singing
of the good days ahead,

19:20.270 --> 19:21.550
giving us hope.

19:25.850 --> 19:27.030
Please remain seated, my dear ministers.

19:27.030 --> 19:29.030
I'll go keep her company for a while.

19:36.660 --> 19:37.830
Speaking of Cen,

19:37.850 --> 19:40.270
he stays in his experimental fields
every day.

19:40.270 --> 19:42.340
Even His Majesty can't summon him away.

19:42.340 --> 19:43.390
What a fool.

19:43.830 --> 19:45.360
Cen is not a fool.

19:45.390 --> 19:47.720
He's a person of utmost purity and virtue.

19:47.930 --> 19:49.890
Without his cultivation methods,

19:50.030 --> 19:51.510
even if our performance is excellent

19:51.510 --> 19:52.400
and our strategies brilliant,

19:52.400 --> 19:54.110
it would all be like a castle in the air,

19:54.110 --> 19:55.400
without foundation.

19:55.630 --> 19:57.010
Er Lan is right.

19:58.480 --> 20:00.330
That's Lord Er to you.

20:02.390 --> 20:03.720
I haven't congratulated you yet.

20:03.720 --> 20:05.670
You gained the Minister of Rite's favor
so quickly

20:05.670 --> 20:07.230
and received an official promotion.

20:07.230 --> 20:07.790
Lord Er,

20:08.030 --> 20:08.830
I toast to you.

20:11.380 --> 20:12.020
Li.

20:12.530 --> 20:13.300
Li.

20:14.480 --> 20:15.810
I know you're upset, Li.

20:15.990 --> 20:17.240
I had a bad temper that day.

20:17.240 --> 20:18.070
Please don't take offense.

20:18.070 --> 20:19.480
I'll punish myself with a drink.

20:19.480 --> 20:19.940
No need.

20:21.160 --> 20:22.220
A toast from Lord Er

20:23.070 --> 20:24.270
is beyond my station.

20:24.400 --> 20:24.880
Right.

20:25.790 --> 20:27.720
If he hadn't stolen your credit that day,

20:27.720 --> 20:29.180
you'd be the one promoted.

20:33.080 --> 20:35.790
The Salt-for-Services Policy
was Li's idea.

20:35.820 --> 20:37.090
I merely conveyed it.

20:37.440 --> 20:39.200
When His Majesty rewards merit,

20:39.200 --> 20:41.010
he won't forget your contribution, Li.

20:41.010 --> 20:42.210
What won't he forget?

20:43.270 --> 20:45.110
What about me needs to be remembered?

20:45.110 --> 20:46.030
I've said it before—

20:46.030 --> 20:47.630
my ambitions lie elsewhere!

20:48.000 --> 20:48.310
Li.

20:48.310 --> 20:48.910
Step back!

20:52.490 --> 20:54.610
Indeed, Li.

20:54.790 --> 20:55.850
So noble and proud,

20:55.920 --> 20:57.000
with such lofty aspirations.

20:57.000 --> 20:59.400
Ready to join court today
and die tomorrow.

20:59.440 --> 21:02.370
-Is that what you think—
-Indeed that's what I think.

21:05.300 --> 21:05.700
You...

21:06.200 --> 21:06.720
Fine!

21:07.000 --> 21:07.850
I'll live!

21:08.590 --> 21:09.310
Live well.

21:10.790 --> 21:12.060
How inappropriate!

21:13.890 --> 21:16.830
It appears Yan millet
is indeed the most drought-resistant

21:16.830 --> 21:17.890
and grows the best.

21:17.960 --> 21:19.650
Though planted in late autumn

21:19.790 --> 21:21.590
without sufficient irrigation,

21:21.590 --> 21:22.790
in just a month or so,

21:23.030 --> 21:24.230
it's grown this well.

21:24.720 --> 21:25.480
Lord Cen,

21:25.750 --> 21:27.340
could you, like you did before,

21:27.340 --> 21:29.740
determine what soil Yan millet suits best,

21:29.970 --> 21:32.030
and how to irrigate and fertilize it?

21:37.500 --> 21:38.360
I

21:38.790 --> 21:40.250
will certainly do my best.

21:41.920 --> 21:42.570
Lord Cen,

21:44.000 --> 21:45.660
please take care of yourself.

21:46.510 --> 21:48.110
Don't worry, Your Highness.

21:48.110 --> 21:48.720
I

21:49.160 --> 21:51.090
will do my best to live a bit longer.

21:51.200 --> 21:53.280
To spend your remaining life like this,

21:53.280 --> 21:54.080
is it worth it?

21:57.720 --> 21:59.520
I have witnessed with my own eyes

22:00.000 --> 22:02.260
people starving to death during famine.

22:03.840 --> 22:06.920
I've also seen mothers
with their infants in swaddling clothes

22:06.920 --> 22:08.680
who never woke again

22:09.800 --> 22:11.100
while fleeing famine.

22:13.080 --> 22:15.080
Everyone lives in the face of death.

22:18.710 --> 22:20.510
To be able to foresee one's death

22:21.070 --> 22:22.870
might be a blessing in disguise.

22:25.720 --> 22:27.250
However, at the very least,

22:28.880 --> 22:31.140
I do not wish to see
the people of this land

22:31.480 --> 22:32.880
die of starvation again.

22:41.440 --> 22:43.040
When my time comes to depart,

22:43.730 --> 22:45.730
I only wish that where my bones rest,

22:45.920 --> 22:48.120
there will be peace throughout the land

22:49.000 --> 22:50.330
and abundant harvests.

22:54.240 --> 22:54.960
Well said.

22:55.680 --> 22:56.680
Excellently put.

22:59.550 --> 23:00.350
Your Majesty.

23:00.400 --> 23:01.260
Your Highness.

23:03.270 --> 23:03.800
Cen,

23:04.510 --> 23:06.170
it's rare to have everyone gathered today.

23:06.170 --> 23:08.850
Would you be willing to set aside
your agricultural work for a moment

23:08.850 --> 23:10.070
and join us, your old friends,

23:10.070 --> 23:10.920
for a drink?

23:18.420 --> 23:18.880
Please.

23:33.830 --> 23:35.260
When I read the novel,

23:36.000 --> 23:38.310
I enjoyed the exciting grand scenes—

23:38.920 --> 23:39.920
power struggles,

23:40.440 --> 23:41.240
epic battles,

23:42.440 --> 23:45.350
watching protagonists
rise from nothing and turn evil,

23:45.350 --> 23:48.480
and the tearing apart of scoundrels
and scheming women.

23:48.710 --> 23:51.110
When I read "Devil's Favorite Concubine,"

23:51.270 --> 23:52.510
I skipped all the parts

23:52.510 --> 23:53.920
where Cen Jintian was fervently farming

23:53.920 --> 23:54.790
completely.

23:57.790 --> 24:00.120
But after coming to this world, I realized

24:01.240 --> 24:02.260
he was the one

24:02.960 --> 24:05.690
who truly saved
countless people from disaster.

24:06.400 --> 24:07.550
To have such a life

24:08.750 --> 24:10.480
is certainly not a waste, is it?

24:11.130 --> 24:12.590
Don't belittle yourself.

24:13.190 --> 24:13.960
You too are

24:14.720 --> 24:16.380
saving people from disaster.

24:17.200 --> 24:17.640
Me?

24:20.070 --> 24:21.710
Helping the dynasty survive the drought,

24:21.020 --> 24:24.010
♪ Standing in the hurricane,
watching the fire rise ♪

24:22.640 --> 24:23.970
objectively speaking,

24:24.310 --> 24:25.750
you should go down in history.

24:24.330 --> 24:27.030
♪ Dancing on the blade's edge, I thread
through blood, writing my wild ode ♪

24:27.300 --> 24:28.250
♪ I am not one of the gentle ones ♪

24:28.280 --> 24:31.820
♪ How could my thoughts
be tethered to the soft begonia?  ♪

24:28.960 --> 24:29.410
Sure.

24:31.750 --> 24:33.110
I don't want to waste this life either.

24:33.110 --> 24:34.560
♪ Do not speak to me
of what's inappropriate ♪

24:34.580 --> 24:36.060
♪ I am the moral order ♪

24:36.000 --> 24:37.030
According to the original novel

24:36.210 --> 24:39.190
♪ The gleam of the blade
tempers feathers into a phantom Phoenix  ♪

24:37.510 --> 24:40.090
Prince Duan paid the highest price
to ascend the throne.

24:39.320 --> 24:40.240
♪ And these Phoenix bones of mine ♪

24:40.310 --> 24:45.200
♪ Empower me
to pierce through the wind and waves ♪

24:40.640 --> 24:43.240
So I'll defeat him
at the lowest cost possible.

24:43.510 --> 24:43.840
Sure.

24:45.310 --> 24:46.850
Preventing the drought
is just the first step.

24:46.680 --> 24:48.310
♪ Allow me ♪

24:47.310 --> 24:49.000
In the future,
he will wage war against Yan State.

24:48.360 --> 24:50.910
♪ To not linger in shame,
to not give way ♪

24:50.320 --> 24:51.930
One general's success
is built on countless deaths.

24:51.330 --> 24:53.820
♪ To not be faithless,
to not admit defeat ♪

24:52.590 --> 24:54.320
Let's prevent him from fighting at all.

24:54.320 --> 24:57.210
♪ A body of stubborn pride
rises to shout that I ♪

24:54.960 --> 24:55.310
Sure.

24:55.780 --> 24:57.510
I remember some details about Yan State.

24:57.310 --> 24:59.870
♪ Was never a creature
meant for the shallows ♪

24:57.720 --> 24:59.250
This war isn't inevitable.

24:59.590 --> 25:00.160
So,

25:00.200 --> 25:01.270
♪ Allow me ♪

25:01.310 --> 25:02.170
let's do it in a diplomatic way—

25:01.650 --> 25:02.980
♪ To never pause ♪

25:02.640 --> 25:03.400
let's ask for peace negotiations.

25:03.400 --> 25:04.400
♪ Allow me ♪

25:03.790 --> 25:04.310
Sure.

25:04.580 --> 25:05.950
♪ To dare to shatter my bones ♪

25:06.220 --> 25:12.030
♪ Wherever I stand,
I dare to write a legend of glory ♪

25:06.790 --> 25:07.790
Are you laughing?

25:08.640 --> 25:09.300
No, I'm not.

25:09.880 --> 25:10.810
You clearly are.

25:11.750 --> 25:12.880
I just find it absurd

25:13.640 --> 25:15.240
that everything we're doing

25:15.370 --> 25:16.400
is all in a book.

25:18.600 --> 25:19.930
It feels quite surreal.

25:21.590 --> 25:23.190
I've thought about this too.

25:34.480 --> 25:35.680
It feels like a paradox.

25:34.850 --> 25:36.230
♪ Allow me ♪

25:36.250 --> 25:38.700
♪ To not linger in shame,
to not give way ♪

25:37.510 --> 25:38.670
How can you be sure

25:39.280 --> 25:41.710
♪ To not be faithless,
to not admit defeat ♪

25:40.200 --> 25:41.730
that the real world outside

25:42.200 --> 25:43.320
isn't just another novel?

25:42.280 --> 25:45.180
♪ A body of stubborn pride
rises to shout that I ♪

25:45.210 --> 25:47.790
♪ Was never a creature
meant for the shallows ♪

25:48.230 --> 25:49.360
♪ Allow me ♪

25:48.960 --> 25:50.000
I indeed don't know.

25:49.610 --> 25:51.030
♪ To never pause ♪

25:51.270 --> 25:52.320
♪ Allow me ♪

25:51.610 --> 25:52.280
So,

25:52.650 --> 25:54.040
♪ To dare to shatter my bones ♪

25:53.480 --> 25:54.890
how can we be certain

25:54.290 --> 26:02.130
♪ Wherever I stand,
I dare to write a legend of glory ♪

25:55.720 --> 25:57.190
that we truly exist?

26:01.350 --> 26:02.810
No point overthinking it.

26:03.880 --> 26:05.830
Even knowing my fate ends in death,

26:07.270 --> 26:08.730
I still want to accomplish

26:08.790 --> 26:10.190
more things before I die.

26:10.920 --> 26:11.270
Sure.

26:12.160 --> 26:13.820
Why do you keep saying "sure"?

26:13.960 --> 26:14.690
Then I'll say

26:15.440 --> 26:17.370
I'll risk my life to accompany you.

26:18.520 --> 26:19.320
Your Majesty!

26:21.640 --> 26:22.350
What's wrong?

26:22.350 --> 26:23.150
Your Majesty,

26:23.350 --> 26:24.110
we've discovered

26:24.110 --> 26:26.200
someone lurking suspiciously
in the forest.

26:26.200 --> 26:27.110
Though it's just one person,

26:27.110 --> 26:28.440
they are highly skilled in martial arts.

26:28.440 --> 26:30.350
Lord Bei Zhou has gone to deal with them.

26:30.350 --> 26:32.880
He ordered us to escort the two of you
back to the palace first.

26:32.880 --> 26:34.410
Only one assassin was sent.

26:35.440 --> 26:37.900
This doesn't seem
like Prince Duan's style.

26:39.680 --> 26:40.610
Keep them alive.

26:40.800 --> 26:42.070
Have Bei Zhou capture them

26:42.070 --> 26:43.110
for interrogation.

26:43.110 --> 26:45.110
Lord Bei Zhou hasn't beaten him yet.

26:45.550 --> 26:46.000
What?

27:00.110 --> 27:01.510
Was there such a character

27:01.510 --> 27:02.770
in the original novel?

27:04.030 --> 27:05.610
I don't remember there being one.

27:05.610 --> 27:08.740
Bei Zhou is the strongest fighter
in the original story,

27:09.240 --> 27:10.770
never having met his match.

27:11.400 --> 27:13.600
This person who appeared out of nowhere

27:14.160 --> 27:15.480
is quite suspicious.

28:10.920 --> 28:11.850
Keep them alive!

28:15.890 --> 28:16.530
Yes, yes.

28:16.710 --> 28:17.640
Hold your blade!

28:17.680 --> 28:19.640
I'm not an assassin. Can't you tell?

28:19.640 --> 28:21.070
If you were really an assassin,

28:21.070 --> 28:22.870
I would have killed you already.

28:23.750 --> 28:25.310
You wouldn't still be alive.

28:25.310 --> 28:26.040
I surrender.

28:26.550 --> 28:27.610
Isn't that enough?

28:31.830 --> 28:32.490
Who are you?

28:33.240 --> 28:34.240
My surname is Bai.

28:35.510 --> 28:36.570
You can call me Bai.

28:49.400 --> 28:50.000
Sir.

28:50.510 --> 28:51.880
Let's talk things through nicely.

28:51.880 --> 28:53.140
Why are you doing this?

28:56.030 --> 28:56.430
Speak.

28:57.680 --> 28:58.740
Where are you from?

29:01.960 --> 29:02.760
I'll tell you!

29:03.200 --> 29:04.000
The Nameless.

29:04.440 --> 29:05.730
You know the Nameless, right?

29:05.730 --> 29:06.590
He's my master.

29:07.000 --> 29:09.110
My master has been observing the stars

29:09.110 --> 29:09.970
and sent me here

29:10.060 --> 29:10.920
with a message.

29:11.550 --> 29:12.150
It's here.

29:22.070 --> 29:23.870
This is indeed his handwriting.

29:23.900 --> 29:25.160
But I can't understand

29:25.790 --> 29:26.590
what he wrote.

29:26.750 --> 29:28.130
Of course you can't understand.

29:28.130 --> 29:29.420
It's not for you.

29:29.480 --> 29:31.160
It's for the Emperor.

29:34.070 --> 29:35.070
Let me have a look.

29:40.680 --> 29:41.490
Emperor?

29:42.880 --> 29:44.010
You are the Emperor?

29:44.160 --> 29:45.240
A living Emperor!

29:45.780 --> 29:48.450
Master, I saw the living Emperor!

29:56.930 --> 29:58.850
The Imperial Throne finds a new master;

29:58.850 --> 30:00.920
the Polaris restores the light in the sky.

30:00.920 --> 30:02.850
A dark omen of royal blood and ruin;

30:03.480 --> 30:05.610
fortune and calamity hang by a thread.

30:05.680 --> 30:07.340
Five stars align,

30:07.880 --> 30:10.010
amidst despair, great fortune rises.

30:13.590 --> 30:15.920
The Imperial Throne finds a new master...

30:19.500 --> 30:20.540
Oh, god.

30:20.860 --> 30:23.000
This person clearly knows your identity.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.200
We've met someone
with true foresight.

30:28.550 --> 30:29.170
Mr. Bei,

30:29.680 --> 30:31.110
do you know the Nameless?

30:31.750 --> 30:33.410
I've known him for many years.

30:33.920 --> 30:35.520
He's skilled in divination.

30:36.200 --> 30:37.860
All his prophecies come true.

30:38.330 --> 30:40.060
He must be sending this message

30:40.480 --> 30:42.520
because he must have foreseen
that you, Dan,

30:42.520 --> 30:43.980
can safeguard the empire.

30:46.440 --> 30:47.110
This kid

30:47.770 --> 30:49.700
is using techniques taught by him.

30:49.920 --> 30:51.380
He should be trustworthy.

30:51.590 --> 30:52.350
Yes.

30:55.120 --> 30:56.960
Master said you're exceptionally talented.

30:56.960 --> 30:58.400
He told me to learn from you.

30:58.400 --> 30:59.460
You're now serving

30:59.800 --> 31:01.130
as the Emperor's guard?

31:02.010 --> 31:02.760
Let me join!

31:03.510 --> 31:04.910
Bei Zhou alone is enough.

31:05.550 --> 31:06.010
Mr. Bei.

31:06.620 --> 31:07.220
Let him go.

31:09.830 --> 31:11.440
He's a godsent elite soldier.

31:11.440 --> 31:12.550
Mr. Bei vouches for him too.

31:12.550 --> 31:13.810
Won't you reconsider?

31:14.550 --> 31:15.880
Master was being kind

31:16.110 --> 31:17.710
sending me here to serve you.

31:17.720 --> 31:19.050
I'm so good at fighting.

31:19.110 --> 31:20.550
Even if I'm not to be your guard,

31:20.550 --> 31:21.440
I can at least

31:21.790 --> 31:23.450
protect this beautiful lady.

31:29.770 --> 31:31.100
Come with us first then.

31:32.550 --> 31:32.920
Sure!

31:33.750 --> 31:34.440
Untie me.

31:35.200 --> 31:35.660
Mr. Bei.

31:35.880 --> 31:36.570
Did you make this?

31:36.570 --> 31:37.230
-Yes.
-Bro.

31:37.270 --> 31:38.000
-For fun.
-Give me a hand.

31:38.000 --> 31:39.200
-Awesome.
-Untie me.

31:40.640 --> 31:41.090
Hey!

31:41.510 --> 31:42.940
Come on, untie me!

31:43.310 --> 31:44.280
Don't leave!

31:52.030 --> 31:54.830
Didn't you get the message
from the secret guards?

31:56.920 --> 31:57.480
I did.

31:58.670 --> 32:00.130
You didn't want me to come.

32:00.690 --> 32:02.750
But Master kept urging me
to come every day,

32:02.750 --> 32:05.350
saying there'll be endless trouble
if you don't rid of the demonic consort.

32:05.350 --> 32:06.640
I'm caught in the middle.

32:06.640 --> 32:07.770
Can't listen to you,

32:07.790 --> 32:09.520
and can't listen to him either.

32:11.310 --> 32:12.270
Life is tough.

32:18.880 --> 32:19.810
Everywhere I go,

32:19.920 --> 32:20.850
I search around.

32:21.400 --> 32:21.880
These

32:22.680 --> 32:24.740
are all folk remedies for headaches.

32:24.920 --> 32:27.250
Maybe it's time to give up.

32:27.590 --> 32:28.160
No way.

32:28.590 --> 32:30.920
This is one of the tasks
Master assigned me.

32:30.920 --> 32:33.030
Since he predicted
I could help you find the cure,

32:33.030 --> 32:34.030
I definitely can.

32:37.160 --> 32:37.830
Fine.

32:43.790 --> 32:44.340
Here.

33:00.310 --> 33:01.770
Don't you dislike sweets?

33:02.550 --> 33:04.810
Why are there so many snacks in your room?

33:05.960 --> 33:07.490
Specially prepared for me?

33:11.560 --> 33:12.700
[The Imperial Throne finds a new master;
the Polaris restores the light in the sky.
A dark omen of royal blood and ruin;]

33:12.720 --> 33:14.220
[fortune and calamity hang by a thread.
Five stars align,
amidst despair, great fortune rises.]

33:12.880 --> 33:13.810
I never expected

33:14.020 --> 33:15.950
to see Master's little note again.

33:16.750 --> 33:18.010
Good thing you kept it.

33:18.440 --> 33:19.100
Otherwise,

33:19.720 --> 33:21.640
I really couldn't find a reason
to come back.

33:21.640 --> 33:23.350
You've learned to steal from me now.

33:23.350 --> 33:24.790
How can you call it stealing?

33:24.790 --> 33:25.960
I just borrowed it.

33:26.440 --> 33:27.440
It's returned now,

33:27.440 --> 33:28.900
isn't it?

33:33.960 --> 33:35.400
I went through all this trouble

33:35.400 --> 33:36.750
to help you fool

33:37.070 --> 33:38.730
that beautiful lady of yours.

33:40.830 --> 33:41.990
Show some respect.

33:43.070 --> 33:44.330
She's a Noble Consort.

33:46.400 --> 33:47.930
From now on, in front of her,

33:48.270 --> 33:49.600
pretend you just met me.

33:50.030 --> 33:51.490
Don't give anything away.

33:51.880 --> 33:52.370
Okay.

33:52.550 --> 33:53.000
Got it.

33:58.070 --> 33:58.720
So

33:59.510 --> 34:01.640
is she the one you've been waiting for?

34:05.920 --> 34:06.640
No.

34:07.510 --> 34:08.639
It was someone else.

34:22.760 --> 34:24.590
I was waiting for the wrong person.

34:24.590 --> 34:26.250
But she came at the right time.

34:26.300 --> 34:27.360
If she hadn't come,

34:28.960 --> 34:30.469
I would have been dead already.

34:30.469 --> 34:31.480
Am I too stupid,

34:32.070 --> 34:33.330
or are you being vague?

34:35.330 --> 34:36.659
You're just too stupid.

34:37.230 --> 34:38.560
You like her, don't you?

34:45.659 --> 34:47.659
Zhang San's Diary.

34:57.490 --> 34:59.620
Move that flower a bit more to the left.

35:00.140 --> 35:02.000
-A little more to the left.
-Okay.

35:03.110 --> 35:06.540
[The late Empress Dowager]

35:03.150 --> 35:04.750
Too much. Move it right a bit.

35:05.670 --> 35:07.220
Lift that grass up a little.

35:08.570 --> 35:10.100
Yes, a bit more to the right.

35:13.610 --> 35:14.550
Crown Prince.

35:17.290 --> 35:18.800
I pay my respects to you, Grandmother.

35:18.800 --> 35:20.450
May the Your Majesty be blessed.

35:20.450 --> 35:22.850
Why are you here

35:23.850 --> 35:25.370
instead of studying in the library?

35:25.370 --> 35:26.770
Grandmother,

35:27.330 --> 35:30.460
His Majesty canceled the Flower Festival
a few days ago.

35:30.520 --> 35:33.450
But I saw these hydrangeas blooming
so beautifully,

35:34.040 --> 35:36.700
and it would be a shame
to leave them unattended,

35:36.890 --> 35:38.820
so I thought I'd arrange them a bit.

35:39.520 --> 35:41.920
By the time of your birthday, Grandmother,

35:42.160 --> 35:43.700
they will be in full bloom.

35:45.730 --> 35:47.740
They can be a birthday gift for you.

35:50.520 --> 35:52.330
How thoughtful of you.

35:56.370 --> 35:57.250
However,

35:57.770 --> 36:00.590
I notice the arrangement of these flowers

36:01.560 --> 36:03.560
seems to have some special meaning.

36:05.190 --> 36:06.720
Take all these things away.

36:07.000 --> 36:08.200
You may leave for now.

36:08.200 --> 36:09.020
-Yes.
-Yes.

36:15.970 --> 36:17.650
You have a discerning eye, Grandmother.

36:17.650 --> 36:18.230
Look.

36:18.910 --> 36:21.370
This depicts two dragons
playing with a pearl,

36:21.370 --> 36:22.900
symbolizing good fortune.

36:22.970 --> 36:23.660
Absurd!

36:25.970 --> 36:28.810
Great Xia can only have one true dragon.

36:30.390 --> 36:31.770
Your mother died early,

36:32.200 --> 36:34.660
and the Emperor
has already found a new love.

36:34.930 --> 36:36.860
Soon he will appoint a new Empress.

36:38.160 --> 36:38.960
In the future,

36:39.040 --> 36:41.160
there may well be more Crown Princes.

36:42.810 --> 36:44.490
In this vast palace,

36:45.200 --> 36:46.530
with all its intrigues,

36:48.330 --> 36:51.110
only I truly care for you.

36:51.980 --> 36:53.040
Do you understand?

36:54.790 --> 36:56.560
You've misunderstood, Grandmother.

36:56.560 --> 36:58.020
The two dragons I planted—

36:58.370 --> 36:59.970
one represents you, Grandmother,

36:59.970 --> 37:01.230
and the other is me.

37:02.410 --> 37:04.600
You are the mother figure of the empire,

37:04.600 --> 37:06.130
presiding over the palace,

37:06.520 --> 37:08.330
supremely noble—

37:08.640 --> 37:11.040
the auspicious dragon protecting
the imperial family.

37:11.040 --> 37:12.550
I, with all my heart,

37:13.040 --> 37:13.770
only wish

37:14.160 --> 37:15.970
to be filial by your side

37:16.680 --> 37:18.800
and serve the empire,

37:19.480 --> 37:21.940
as the little dragon
under your protection.

37:28.520 --> 37:30.040
Come, get up.

37:35.080 --> 37:37.330
You truly are my good grandson.

37:40.560 --> 37:41.370
Rest assured,

37:42.560 --> 37:45.210
as long as I am around in this palace,

37:46.080 --> 37:47.410
those sordid affairs

37:48.080 --> 37:50.140
will not interfere with your future.

37:51.770 --> 37:53.290
You, my little dragon,

37:54.200 --> 37:56.410
are the only true dragon in this palace.

37:57.770 --> 37:58.830
Do you understand?

38:03.080 --> 38:04.480
Thank you, Grandmother.

38:12.260 --> 38:21.080
[SOS]

38:24.330 --> 38:25.600
If you are like me,

38:25.810 --> 38:26.870
leave me a message.

38:27.200 --> 38:28.420
I want to meet you.
